<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="165" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/869: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in France (<persName type="to">Marriner</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-30T15:00:00-05:00">September 30, 1932—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>345. From Ambassador Edge.</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <p>Re your 564, September 30, noon, no possible justification for French
                                newspapers to make such assumption. You may without qualification
                                state that Ambassador Edge is at the moment in Washington discussing
                                details of French counter proposal and full report which does not
                                present insurmountable difficulties will be in Embassy’s possession
                                early next week.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>